challenges.explanation:
The quality of ingredients (flour, water, salt) varies significantly based on season, supplier, and storage conditions.  Automated systems must constantly monitor these inputs and adjust processes accordingly, a task that’s complicated by unpredictable variations. Furthermore, accurately assessing the freshness of ingredients – particularly the activity of the yeast – is difficult, as this changes over time and is heavily influenced by environmental factors. Current sensors lack the sensitivity to detect these subtle changes, making proactive adjustments challenging."
